WEBVTT

00:26.109 --> 00:29.070
Should I stay or should I go now?

00:30.697 --> 00:34.117
Should I stay or should I go now?

00:35.702 --> 00:38.580
If I go, there will be trouble

00:39.247 --> 00:42.083
And if I stay, it will be double

00:43.168 --> 00:49.174
So, come on and let me know
Should I stay or should I go?

03:49.312 --> 03:51.522
At long last,

03:52.815 --> 03:54.192
we can begin.

04:22.387 --> 04:23.846
You and I,

04:25.014 --> 04:31.562
we are going to do
such beautiful things together, William.

04:32.730 --> 04:36.609
Such beautiful things.

06:14.916 --> 06:16.042
Holly.

06:17.210 --> 06:18.211
Holly!

06:19.796 --> 06:20.838
Holly!

06:20.922 --> 06:22.507
I've been calling you.

06:22.590 --> 06:23.674
I'm sorry.

06:23.758 --> 06:25.259
Could you round up the troops?

06:28.513 --> 06:29.972
Breakfast!

06:30.056 --> 06:31.516
Coming!

06:32.100 --> 06:33.393
Nance, come on.

06:34.769 --> 06:37.230
Let me in,
or I'm gonna whiz on the floor right here.

06:38.356 --> 06:39.732
Sorry, Mrs. Byers.

06:39.816 --> 06:41.109
Whiz away.

06:41.943 --> 06:42.944
Wow.

06:44.862 --> 06:46.030
Shit.

06:47.532 --> 06:48.908
Breakfast!

06:50.576 --> 06:52.412
Shit, dude, we overslept.

06:52.495 --> 06:55.081
-I thought you were setting an alarm.
-I thought you were.

07:00.378 --> 07:04.674
-It's not always Jonathan's fault.
-It's always Jonathan's…

07:04.757 --> 07:06.843
It wasn't my fault. I told you…

07:07.844 --> 07:09.762
Holly, can you pass the bacon?

07:10.555 --> 07:12.348
Holly! Bacon!

07:15.518 --> 07:17.937
-You need to just drop it.
-Whatever you want.

07:18.020 --> 07:20.231
You don't need it. You're crazy, huh?

07:22.191 --> 07:24.777
Karen, do you have any Midol upstairs?

07:29.031 --> 07:31.033
Nancy, dishes in the sink.

07:31.117 --> 07:34.412
Be back at 5:00 or 6:00. Let me know
if you need me to pick up anything.

07:34.495 --> 07:35.872
-Boogie!
-Come on. Hurry up.

07:35.955 --> 07:37.790
-I'm coming.
-Holly, your jacket.

07:37.874 --> 07:39.459
-Here. Don't forget it.
-Thank you.

07:39.542 --> 07:40.418
Hug.

07:40.501 --> 07:41.335
-Bye.
-Bye.

07:41.419 --> 07:44.088
I'm sorry. I can't help clean up.
I'm running late.

07:44.172 --> 07:46.799
It's okay, Joyce, really. I understand.

07:47.884 --> 07:49.218
How much longer?

07:50.470 --> 07:53.723
What do you want me to do, Ted, huh?
Kick 'em to the street?

07:54.223 --> 07:55.892
Is that an option?

08:01.689 --> 08:03.566
Hey, wait up! Wait up!

08:03.649 --> 08:05.109
Come on, we gotta go!

08:08.779 --> 08:11.991
The Morning Squawk, Mike,
we're gonna miss it!

08:12.074 --> 08:15.912
Good morning, Hawkins!
This is WSQK The Squawk!

08:16.704 --> 08:17.580
That's a new one.

08:17.663 --> 08:19.749
It's looking like a regular day
in Hawkins.

08:19.832 --> 08:22.001
Fifty-five degrees, low chance of rain,

08:22.084 --> 08:25.713
medium chance of arrest,
high chance of helicopters.

08:25.796 --> 08:29.592
But general banality aside,
it's an exciting day for me,

08:29.675 --> 08:32.261
your friend, entertainer, and DJ,
Robin Buckley…

08:32.345 --> 08:35.223
Nice to meet you! …AKA Rockin' Robin.

08:35.306 --> 08:37.558
And why is it a big day for me, you ask?

08:37.642 --> 08:40.228
Well, it's my 500th broadcast.

08:40.311 --> 08:43.648
Yeah, you heard that right, folks.
Five-double-O!

08:43.731 --> 08:45.233
Which means it's been even longer

08:45.316 --> 08:48.152
since you've heard the sultry voice
of Jimmy "Fast Hands" Lee.

08:48.236 --> 08:53.074
But while Jimmy was fleeing Hawkins
even faster than he moves those hands,

08:53.157 --> 08:57.245
yours truly was watching slack-jawed
as the earth split open beneath her feet

08:57.328 --> 09:00.456
and coughed up that tsunami
of mysterious dandruff.

09:00.540 --> 09:04.502
And now, I'm stuck here with you,
my fellow quarantine compatriots.

09:04.585 --> 09:08.506
And if I can be brutally honest,
I couldn't be happier.

09:08.589 --> 09:13.594
Because when you really think about it,
why would you want to live anywhere else?

09:13.678 --> 09:16.264
I mean, what town on Earth can match

09:16.347 --> 09:20.059
our very impressive
military-to-civilian ratio?

09:21.394 --> 09:24.313
And those free,
mandatory medical checkups?

09:24.397 --> 09:25.815
I mean, very cool.

09:25.898 --> 09:28.192
'Cause after we inhaled
those springtime snowflakes,

09:28.276 --> 09:29.527
who knows what's wrong with us?

09:29.610 --> 09:32.238
Maybe we're fine, maybe not.

09:32.321 --> 09:33.739
No one knows for sure.

09:33.823 --> 09:39.036
After all, this was a "natural phenomenon
never before seen by man."

09:39.620 --> 09:45.126
A phenomenon now covered up
by a giant metal Band-Aid.

09:45.209 --> 09:48.713
Quite the eyesore,
but hey, great for sledding.

09:48.796 --> 09:53.092
Though seriously, kids, stop sledding
on the giant steel Band-Aid.

09:53.175 --> 09:55.636
You are going to kill yourselves.
Also, the men with guns.

09:55.720 --> 09:58.973
-Go, go, go, go, go!
-They don't like it, not one bit.

09:59.974 --> 10:02.893
While we're on the subject
of things not to do,

10:02.977 --> 10:06.314
please steer clear
of the Military Access Control Zone,

10:06.397 --> 10:10.568
aka the MAC-Z,
or as I like to call it, the Big Mac.

10:11.068 --> 10:13.362
I have no idea what's going on in there,

10:13.446 --> 10:15.489
but I have a gut feeling

10:15.573 --> 10:19.660
there's a pretty good reason
they'd like you to stay away.

10:19.744 --> 10:23.039
But hey, the rest of Hawkins
is still there for you to enjoy.

10:23.122 --> 10:25.541
Someday soon,
they're gonna let us out of here.

10:25.625 --> 10:27.460
In the meantime,
be thankful this is your home,

10:27.543 --> 10:31.047
study for that test,
enjoy that TV dinner, and go on that date.

10:31.130 --> 10:35.426
Which, by the way, is exactly
what yours truly is doing tonight.

10:35.509 --> 10:39.013
That's right. Rockin' Robin has a date,
ladies and gentlemen.

10:41.641 --> 10:44.268
And now, who is this lucky someone?

10:44.352 --> 10:46.646
Well, don't be so nosy, kids.

10:47.480 --> 10:49.065
They know who they are.

10:49.148 --> 10:53.319
That is, if you're listening,
which I hope you are.

10:53.402 --> 10:56.906
Because this next one, it's for you, babe.

11:05.164 --> 11:06.165
What the hell?

11:09.126 --> 11:12.922
Whoa. What's going on?
What the hell? What the hell?

11:14.590 --> 11:17.051
I told you to stop thumbing your nose
at the military.

11:17.134 --> 11:20.388
I was reiterating their goddamn rules,
encouraging compliance.

11:20.471 --> 11:23.140
-Right. No sarcasm there.
-Said the dingus with the rubber chicken.

11:23.224 --> 11:27.311
-These are very serious people, Robin.
-Shit, shit, shit, shit, shit!

11:28.479 --> 11:32.066
Henderson, you copy? Henderson?

11:32.149 --> 11:33.526
Yeah, I copy.

11:34.276 --> 11:37.029
God, you sound swell.
Let me take a wild guess.

11:37.113 --> 11:38.906
You're not calling
to wish me good morning.

11:38.989 --> 11:42.326
It's not exactly a good morning.
We've got a situation at the Squawk.

11:42.410 --> 11:44.495
The signal, it's… it's gone all wonky.

11:44.578 --> 11:46.372
I think Robin finally pissed 'em off.

11:46.455 --> 11:48.624
Doubtful. She was encouraging compliance.

11:48.708 --> 11:49.709
Told you!

11:49.792 --> 11:51.919
The remote radio head's
the more likely culprit.

11:52.002 --> 11:54.088
-The remote what?
-Just read the manual, Steve.

11:54.171 --> 11:55.840
That thing might as well be in Greek.

11:55.923 --> 11:56.799
Then learn Greek!

11:56.882 --> 11:59.677
I can't always be there
to solve your problems for you, Steve.

12:00.428 --> 12:01.470
Henderson?

12:03.097 --> 12:04.098
God!

12:04.724 --> 12:06.642
"Learn Greek." You heard that tone.

12:07.768 --> 12:09.103
You heard that, right?

12:18.821 --> 12:19.822
Watch it.

12:27.663 --> 12:29.832
What'd I tell you about that shirt, freak?

12:30.458 --> 12:33.586
Andy asked you a question, freak.
You deaf or what?

12:35.463 --> 12:38.632
For his sake, I hope he is,
because I thought I was pretty damn clear

12:38.716 --> 12:40.676
when I said
I didn't wanna see you in that shirt.

12:40.760 --> 12:42.386
You also told me
to stop screwing your mom,

12:42.470 --> 12:43.929
and that didn't stop me, did it?

12:46.474 --> 12:48.476
-Something funny, Henderson?
-Let go.

12:48.976 --> 12:50.811
Hellfire is over, you hear me?

12:50.895 --> 12:52.605
Let go.

12:52.688 --> 12:54.940
Or what? What are you gonna do?

12:56.442 --> 12:58.444
Stop! Andy! Stop!

12:58.527 --> 12:59.403
Hey!

13:05.743 --> 13:06.744
Well, well.

13:07.787 --> 13:08.996
If it isn't the traitor.

13:13.000 --> 13:15.753
Remember that time
my sister kicked your balls so hard,

13:15.836 --> 13:17.213
you limped for a week?

13:18.422 --> 13:19.924
Yeah, if you touch Dustin again,

13:20.508 --> 13:23.010
I'll kick 'em so hard
they'll pop like water balloons.

13:23.093 --> 13:24.637
I say kick away.

13:24.720 --> 13:26.263
Stop this meathead from reproducing

13:26.347 --> 13:29.308
and further infecting the world
with his unique brand of idiocy.

13:34.563 --> 13:38.359
Hope you brought a change of clothes.
No one wants to see that shit.

13:49.453 --> 13:51.247
You've gotta stop provoking them, man.

13:51.330 --> 13:53.123
Oh, so this is my fault?

13:53.207 --> 13:56.085
-For what? Wearing a T-shirt?
-You know it's more than a T-shirt.

13:56.168 --> 13:58.045
I can't be like you
and turn the other cheek

13:58.128 --> 14:00.881
while they spread their bullshit
about Hellfire, about Eddie.

14:00.965 --> 14:02.091
Eddie never gave a rat's ass

14:02.174 --> 14:04.468
about what those mouth breathers
were saying about him.

14:04.552 --> 14:07.221
What he would care about
is finding and killing Vecna.

14:07.304 --> 14:11.350
Do you seriously think
I don't care about that, Mike? Really?

14:11.433 --> 14:13.936
I think you're fighting two battles.
You need to be fighting one.

14:14.019 --> 14:16.814
Mike's right, Dustin.
What if you get seriously hurt?

14:16.897 --> 14:18.190
You're drawing attention.

14:18.274 --> 14:21.777
Remember what Hop said.
We need to keep our heads down.

14:21.861 --> 14:24.613
-Follow the rules. Blend in.
-Stay focused on our next crawl.

14:24.697 --> 14:26.448
Do you even hear yourselves right now?

14:26.532 --> 14:30.035
Blend in? Follow the rules?
That's not what we've ever done.

14:30.119 --> 14:32.413
-Jesus Christ.
-We stay true to ourselves.

14:32.496 --> 14:34.456
We're supposed to stay true
to our friends.

14:34.540 --> 14:37.585
We stand up for what's right,
no matter the cost.

14:37.668 --> 14:38.878
You're not listening to us.

14:38.961 --> 14:41.130
No, you're not.

14:41.213 --> 14:42.590
Dustin!

14:43.841 --> 14:45.718
-Unbelievable.
-Let him go.

15:15.831 --> 15:16.832
Come on.

15:16.916 --> 15:17.833
Move, move!

15:34.350 --> 15:36.393
You're a fast little shit, huh?

15:43.108 --> 15:44.276
It's not her.

15:44.777 --> 15:47.029
Another goddamn burnout, sir.

15:49.531 --> 15:50.532
Get her out of here.

15:55.412 --> 15:56.246
Shit!

16:31.448 --> 16:33.033
Twelve minutes, 33 seconds.

16:33.117 --> 16:34.326
It's a new record.

16:37.371 --> 16:40.582
So? How are we feeling?

16:40.666 --> 16:41.542
Okay.

16:42.126 --> 16:43.043
Okay?

16:43.127 --> 16:45.963
Come on, that was 12:33!

16:46.046 --> 16:47.423
It's four seconds too slow.

16:47.506 --> 16:49.717
I lost one second on the climb,
two seconds at the log.

16:49.800 --> 16:52.136
-Hey.
-I can make my bus jump sooner.

16:52.219 --> 16:55.305
That'll save me two more seconds.
That gets me under 12:30.

16:55.389 --> 16:58.017
El, you have to take it easy on yourself.

16:58.100 --> 17:00.436
-You think Henry's going easy?
-You know what I think?

17:01.020 --> 17:04.815
I think we still have
some more of that waffle mix.

17:04.898 --> 17:09.737
And I think we should celebrate
this record time with a stack of those.

17:09.820 --> 17:14.658
And then maybe we could watch
a Miami Vice marathon.

17:16.577 --> 17:18.454
I can beat the time. Reset it.

17:19.621 --> 17:21.498
If you're tired,
you're gonna injure yourself.

17:21.582 --> 17:22.416
Reset it!

17:41.935 --> 17:42.936
Heads up!

17:53.864 --> 17:55.741
Hey, hey. How you doing?

17:55.824 --> 17:59.787
Austin Millbarge, ID 4528-niner.

17:59.870 --> 18:01.997
That's me.

18:18.680 --> 18:21.100
I swear to God,
this stupid thing does not exist.

18:21.183 --> 18:23.519
-Can someone try Dustin again?
-He turned off his walkie.

18:23.602 --> 18:25.646
-What's up with him lately?
-Don't get me started.

18:25.729 --> 18:26.897
Yeah, please don't.

18:26.980 --> 18:28.148
-Hey!
-Huh?

18:29.024 --> 18:30.025
Got it.

18:35.364 --> 18:37.199
Wait, wait, wait. There it is, yeah.

18:37.282 --> 18:38.700
Remote radio head, yeah.

18:39.910 --> 18:44.039
And, uh, where exactly are we gonna find
this remote thingamajig?

18:51.171 --> 18:52.172
I don't see it.

18:52.965 --> 18:54.758
It's up there somewhere.

18:54.842 --> 18:55.926
It's gotta be.

18:56.468 --> 19:01.557
So, I guess somebody's gotta climb
to the tippy top of this bad boy and…

19:03.058 --> 19:06.353
Without a harness or anything,
it seems kind of dangerous.

19:07.062 --> 19:10.065
AKA job for good old Steve Harrington.

19:10.149 --> 19:11.984
-No third person, please.
-All right.

19:12.067 --> 19:13.443
I, uh…

19:13.527 --> 19:16.738
I actually think this might be
a better job for Jonathan Byers.

19:17.364 --> 19:21.201
I'm like one quarter monkey, dude.
I got this, Byers. Don't sweat it.

19:23.954 --> 19:25.205
Uh, voltage!

19:25.289 --> 19:26.915
Unless you wanna fry.

19:26.999 --> 19:28.000
Yeah, I know.

19:29.376 --> 19:30.294
I'm not an idiot.

19:42.222 --> 19:44.391
Whoa, dude, what are you doing?

19:44.892 --> 19:47.352
I got this, dude. Don't sweat it.

19:47.436 --> 19:48.812
Son of a…

20:00.073 --> 20:03.577
What is it about your presence
that brings out their inner Neanderthal?

20:06.121 --> 20:08.582
I thought grocery delivery
wasn't till tomorrow.

20:09.291 --> 20:10.417
Me too.

20:13.837 --> 20:15.631
Ah, come on. Come on.

20:35.901 --> 20:36.777
Shit.

20:40.322 --> 20:41.823
-Whoa.
-Yeah.

20:47.621 --> 20:48.622
Found ya.

20:53.627 --> 20:54.461
Never fails.

20:55.587 --> 20:57.297
-I fixed it!
-I fixed it!

21:06.682 --> 21:07.599
All right.

21:10.102 --> 21:12.771
Santa's brought a full sack today.

21:17.067 --> 21:20.404
A fresh telemetry tag.
Scarcer than hen's teeth, these things.

21:23.782 --> 21:26.243
Enough bullets and shells
for Hop to start a small war,

21:26.326 --> 21:28.537
if he should so choose.

21:29.496 --> 21:31.415
Anyone order a salad?

21:31.915 --> 21:34.126
Grenade salad?

21:34.209 --> 21:37.462
I hid the grenades under the, uh, lettuce.

21:38.255 --> 21:39.256
Okay.

21:40.132 --> 21:42.467
Gatorade for El's battery.

21:42.551 --> 21:43.802
Did someone say Gatorade?

21:44.636 --> 21:46.263
-Let me get one. Thanks.
-Sure.

21:46.346 --> 21:49.016
But I don't think
it's gonna go too well with…

21:50.684 --> 21:51.810
peanut butter!

21:51.893 --> 21:54.604
Boppers! God, I missed these things.

21:54.688 --> 21:55.647
Thanks.

21:55.731 --> 21:57.899
Don't worry, Mr. Byers.
I got you a present too.

21:58.817 --> 22:00.402
I know you're allergic to jazz,

22:00.485 --> 22:04.364
but just give it a whirl.
I think you'll find it quite engaging.

22:07.242 --> 22:10.954
And for the station manager,
the reason for my premature delivery.

22:17.210 --> 22:19.171
A burn? Tonight? But that's--

22:19.254 --> 22:20.297
Too soon, I know.

22:20.380 --> 22:24.926
Whatever they're doing in the Upside Down
evidently needs serious resources.

22:25.010 --> 22:26.470
That's a lot of cargo.

22:26.553 --> 22:31.016
I figure a supply drop this big
takes two hours, minimum.

22:31.099 --> 22:33.560
Which gives Hopper
plenty of time for a crawl.

22:33.643 --> 22:38.982
Maybe tonight's the night
we finally find that bastard and end this.

23:08.470 --> 23:10.013
Hey there, Jake.

23:11.890 --> 23:13.308
You up for a little field trip?

23:16.812 --> 23:19.272
I'm telling you, he's lost his mind.

23:19.356 --> 23:21.566
He told me
he wanted to start Hellfire again.

23:21.650 --> 23:23.318
What? When did he say that?

23:23.944 --> 23:27.155
This weekend. He was talking
about finding the lost sheep.

23:27.239 --> 23:29.116
And we thought the shirt was bad.

23:29.616 --> 23:31.827
I'm telling you, he's lost his damn mind.

23:32.911 --> 23:34.329
Who's lost his damn mind?

23:34.413 --> 23:36.623
-Uh, the--
-Andy!

23:36.706 --> 23:37.582
-Andy!
-Andy.

23:37.666 --> 23:39.126
-Andy lost his mind.
-Yeah.

23:39.209 --> 23:40.961
Like when he came at you this morning.

23:41.044 --> 23:42.629
-Yeah, that was--
-Messed up.

23:42.712 --> 23:43.630
Yeah.

23:44.172 --> 23:45.340
It's rude.

23:49.302 --> 23:51.430
Hey there, friends, this is Rockin' Robin.

23:51.513 --> 23:54.224
Sorry about the abrupt departure.
I hope you survived without me.

23:54.307 --> 23:57.352
We had some annoying
technical difficulties.

23:59.729 --> 24:02.107
But to make it up to you,
we have a very special treat

24:02.190 --> 24:05.360
that's sure to turn your day upside down…

24:07.028 --> 24:08.321
-Holy shit.
-Already?

24:08.405 --> 24:09.489
Paper! Give me paper!

24:11.241 --> 24:12.993
Come on! Will, hurry up!

24:13.076 --> 24:15.620
You're giving love instinctively

24:15.704 --> 24:19.374
Before you start bumping,
here's a few fun facts about the Boss.

24:19.458 --> 24:22.377
She was born Diane
in the North End of Detroit.

24:22.961 --> 24:26.673
Berry Gordy, that's Gordy with a G,
signed her to Motown in 1961.

24:26.756 --> 24:28.675
And one is the key number,

24:28.758 --> 24:30.677
because between 1964 and '67,

24:30.760 --> 24:33.430
the Supremes had ten songs
hit the top of the charts.

24:33.513 --> 24:34.973
That's right, ten.

24:35.056 --> 24:38.143
Then in '78, she tried to make it big
in the movies with The Wiz,

24:38.226 --> 24:40.353
which was a colossal flop-a-roonie.

24:40.437 --> 24:43.148
But, in my personal opinion,
I still dig it.

24:43.231 --> 24:44.983
Michael Jackson as a scarecrow?

24:45.066 --> 24:46.443
Give it a chance.

24:46.526 --> 24:48.445
But make sure you bring
your super-sized popcorn,

24:48.528 --> 24:51.990
because this movie has a run time
of over two hours.

24:52.073 --> 24:53.742
All right, class dismissed.

24:53.825 --> 24:56.703
I hope you were taking notes.
There will be a test later.

24:56.786 --> 24:57.787
Take it away, Diane.

24:59.456 --> 25:00.999
Upside down

25:02.000 --> 25:03.210
Crawl tonight.

25:03.293 --> 25:04.294
Come on.

25:04.377 --> 25:05.754
Inside out

25:06.546 --> 25:08.089
'Round and 'round

25:08.173 --> 25:10.175
Upside down

25:10.967 --> 25:14.513
Boy, you turn me inside out

25:14.596 --> 25:16.806
And 'round and 'round

25:18.475 --> 25:20.393
I know you got charm and appeal

25:20.477 --> 25:22.062
You always play the field

25:22.145 --> 25:25.273
I'm crazy to think you're all mine

25:26.525 --> 25:30.445
As long as the sun continues to shine

25:30.529 --> 25:33.657
There's a place in my heart for you
That's the bottom line

25:54.553 --> 25:55.679
All right.

25:55.762 --> 25:58.765
So, assuming Murray's intel is correct,

25:58.848 --> 26:02.310
the supply convoy is set
to reach Hawkins at 10:00 sharp.

26:02.394 --> 26:04.729
Meaning I want Hopper in the tunnels

26:04.813 --> 26:07.524
and en route to MAC-Z no later than 9:00.

26:07.607 --> 26:09.818
Lucas, we'll take
our usual observation post.

26:10.527 --> 26:11.820
Barring unusual traffic,

26:11.903 --> 26:14.406
I expect the convoy
to reach MAC-Z at 10:15.

26:14.489 --> 26:16.449
Once the burn starts
and there's sufficient cover,

26:16.533 --> 26:18.159
we'll signal Hopper, who'll make his move.

26:18.910 --> 26:21.246
And now the crawl begins.

26:21.329 --> 26:23.623
Hop is now in the Upside Down,

26:23.707 --> 26:26.751
traveling at what I hope to be
a gentle 30 miles an hour,

26:26.835 --> 26:27.669
which will allow…

26:27.752 --> 26:30.046
…you and Harrington to follow along
in the Rightside Up.

26:30.130 --> 26:32.674
Just remember,
try and keep the telemetry signal within…

26:32.757 --> 26:35.802
Negative 60 and negative 70 dB.
Easy-peasy.

26:35.885 --> 26:38.388
I expect the convoy
to take the same route as last month.

26:38.471 --> 26:40.557
Main to Cornwallis, one turn.

26:40.640 --> 26:42.350
But if you guys hit any red lights…

26:42.434 --> 26:44.603
-I'll blow through.
-Only if there's no MPs around.

26:44.686 --> 26:48.732
Remember, if you guys get pulled over,
we lose Hop, we're toast.

26:48.815 --> 26:49.899
I got it.

26:49.983 --> 26:53.111
You're gonna travel up Cornwallis
for about six miles.

26:53.612 --> 26:56.156
And as the convoy reaches
this Shell station here…

26:56.239 --> 26:57.866
We radio Hop to disembark.

26:57.949 --> 27:00.118
Which will drop the old man
at the border of G1.

27:00.201 --> 27:05.540
Where he'll have two whole hours
to search for Vecna, which is ample time.

27:05.624 --> 27:07.876
He's cleared zones much faster.

27:07.959 --> 27:12.547
So, all in all,
signs point to another successful crawl.

27:14.591 --> 27:15.884
Is there a problem?

27:16.843 --> 27:18.136
Um…

27:18.970 --> 27:22.057
No. No, I mean, I think it's good.

27:22.641 --> 27:25.018
Yeah, yeah, it's good. It's really good.

27:25.101 --> 27:26.102
It's just, um…

27:26.186 --> 27:30.106
Zone G1 is not that exciting or Vecna-y.

27:30.190 --> 27:32.984
What does it have?
A Circuit City, a couple of houses, and a…

27:33.068 --> 27:37.072
Big Buy? What are the chances
Vecna's shopping for Lucky Charms?

27:37.155 --> 27:38.907
It doesn't matter. We stick to the plan.

27:38.990 --> 27:41.785
We break into the Upside Down
the only way we can,

27:41.868 --> 27:44.120
through the MAC-Z gate,
under the cover of a burn.

27:44.204 --> 27:47.082
Once inside, we search
one zone at a time, methodically,

27:47.165 --> 27:49.084
until we figure out
where he's been hiding.

27:49.668 --> 27:50.669
Unless…

27:51.753 --> 27:53.088
he's already dead.

27:53.588 --> 27:55.423
Again, your plan is great. It's just…

27:56.132 --> 27:58.343
This is crawl what? Are we in the 30s now?

27:58.426 --> 27:59.928
And not a single baddie in sight?

28:00.637 --> 28:02.138
El can't find him in her bath,

28:02.222 --> 28:04.808
and Will hasn't had his goosies
since the shake 'n' quake.

28:04.891 --> 28:06.643
-Goosies?
-And last we saw Vecna,

28:06.726 --> 28:08.853
he was roasting like a turkey
and pumped full of lead.

28:08.937 --> 28:10.605
That was before he fell three stories.

28:10.689 --> 28:12.982
So you ever think
we're scouring a battlefield

28:13.066 --> 28:15.735
that we already, like, won?

28:15.819 --> 28:18.863
Have you forgotten what he showed Nancy?
Hawkins on fire.

28:18.947 --> 28:21.199
-Karen, Holly, everyone dead.
-Yeah, man.

28:21.282 --> 28:24.452
He also showed Max her brother
walking around with a hole in his chest.

28:24.536 --> 28:27.038
That's what he does. He gets in your head
and tries to scare you.

28:27.122 --> 28:30.792
He did a good job because I am scared.
And you should be scared too.

28:30.875 --> 28:34.045
Because if he's still out there,
he's planning to end our world, so…

28:34.129 --> 28:37.674
We don't stop looking.
Even if it takes 100 more crawls, 1,000.

28:37.757 --> 28:39.634
We don't stop until we're goddamn sure

28:39.718 --> 28:44.681
that wrinkled, noseless, rotting bastard
is dead and gone and never coming back.

28:46.141 --> 28:47.183
Everyone in?

28:55.233 --> 28:57.402
I want to see Vecna's heart on a platter.

28:58.236 --> 28:59.654
Just wish I could do it myself.

29:00.905 --> 29:01.906
For Eddie.

29:01.990 --> 29:03.199
-For Eddie.
-For Eddie.

29:03.283 --> 29:06.494
On three, "kill Vecna." One, two, three.

29:06.578 --> 29:07.579
Kill Vecna!

29:09.581 --> 29:11.124
Oh no!

29:12.625 --> 29:16.296
-Military man.
-Wanted to see if you had my back.

29:16.379 --> 29:19.466
Yeah, I have your back.

29:54.709 --> 29:55.960
-Will!
-Will!

29:56.044 --> 29:57.045
Will!

29:57.545 --> 29:59.964
-Hey, are you okay?
-Yeah, it's okay. I'm fine.

30:00.048 --> 30:01.800
Was it him? Was it Vecna?

30:01.883 --> 30:04.052
I don't know.
I just had this crazy feeling,

30:04.135 --> 30:06.346
and then the sky was spinning, and…

30:07.680 --> 30:10.058
I don't know.
I guess maybe it's nothing, right?

30:11.559 --> 30:12.685
I don't know.

30:13.603 --> 30:16.314
Maybe I just get nervous sometimes
before crawls.

30:16.397 --> 30:18.191
Yeah, I… I get nervous too.

30:18.942 --> 30:20.902
But the sky doesn't spin for me.

30:21.486 --> 30:22.779
It ever spin for you?

30:23.905 --> 30:24.906
Maybe he's close.

30:28.993 --> 30:31.663
Okay. Squawk, six o'clock,
not a second later, right?

30:31.746 --> 30:32.831
-Six o'clock.
-Are you okay?

30:32.914 --> 30:33.832
-Yeah.
-You sure?

30:33.915 --> 30:35.792
-Take it slow.
-Okay, yeah.

30:42.340 --> 30:46.594
I'm just trying to get it started.
Ready? Here we go. Come on.

30:47.595 --> 30:51.349
I just gotta get this going,
and then we're gonna have lots of fun.

30:51.432 --> 30:53.059
Blast off!

30:53.142 --> 30:54.686
Derek, stop! Come on! Get off!

30:54.769 --> 30:56.604
-Derek, stop!
-Hold on tight!

30:56.688 --> 30:59.148
-Go away! Derek!
-Try not to puke!

30:59.232 --> 31:00.316
Stop!

31:01.568 --> 31:03.319
-Jerk face!
-Bite me.

31:03.403 --> 31:04.737
You okay? Come here.

31:05.572 --> 31:06.614
Let's get you off.

31:06.698 --> 31:08.575
Oh my… Careful, careful!

31:08.658 --> 31:10.034
You okay?

31:10.743 --> 31:12.871
All right, my dears, playtime's over.

31:14.163 --> 31:14.998
Come on.

31:15.832 --> 31:17.917
What is with that grumpy face?

31:18.001 --> 31:23.965
Come on, we have books to read,
art to create, wisdom to unlock.

31:27.343 --> 31:28.344
Holly?

31:31.973 --> 31:32.932
Hi.

31:34.225 --> 31:36.853
And she can tell Derek to go away too.

31:36.936 --> 31:38.980
He is a jerk face.

31:40.064 --> 31:41.983
Oh yeah, Miss Harris gave me…

31:45.904 --> 31:48.031
But she also said
it wasn't really my fault.

32:19.687 --> 32:23.399
Are you just
going to stand there, Sergeant Ramirez,

32:23.483 --> 32:25.902
or did you have something to report?

32:25.985 --> 32:27.236
Sorry, Dr. Kay.

32:27.320 --> 32:29.614
Yes. Lieutenant Colonel Sullivan,

32:29.697 --> 32:31.783
he tracked down
that lead we spoke about, and--

32:31.866 --> 32:34.327
It was a tremendous success.

32:34.410 --> 32:36.079
No, unfortunately.

32:36.162 --> 32:39.624
I see
they don't teach sarcasm in the ROTC.

32:42.794 --> 32:46.130
If it was good news,
Sullivan would be here himself,

32:46.214 --> 32:49.467
with trumpets and confetti,
I have no doubt.

32:51.636 --> 32:53.429
Don't worry. It doesn't bite.

32:54.305 --> 32:56.265
It does, on occasion, strangle.

32:58.351 --> 32:59.727
Was there anything else?

33:00.395 --> 33:03.564
A new lead, perhaps,
to offer more false hope?

33:03.648 --> 33:04.941
Not yet, Doctor.

33:08.736 --> 33:09.779
Sergeant.

33:11.614 --> 33:16.077
Please tell your commander
that I am running into a wall here.

33:16.160 --> 33:19.038
People are dying, innocent people.

33:20.707 --> 33:22.667
I need the girl.

33:49.402 --> 33:50.987
The last run, what was my time?

33:51.070 --> 33:55.283
I'm not sure. I didn't see.
I was distracted by Diana Ross.

33:55.366 --> 33:56.993
I saved four seconds.

33:57.493 --> 33:58.453
Highly doubt that.

33:58.536 --> 34:00.246
No, no, it was very fast.

34:00.329 --> 34:03.124
One second on the climb,
one with the log, two on the bus.

34:03.207 --> 34:05.334
Great. You did that today.
You can do it again tomorrow.

34:05.418 --> 34:09.213
The crawl is tonight, Hop.
If I'm under 12:30, I can come with you.

34:09.297 --> 34:12.759
-That is what you promised.
-Yeah, I promised that. I promised it.

34:12.842 --> 34:14.635
But I didn't see it.

34:15.887 --> 34:17.764
So blame Diana.

34:32.070 --> 34:34.447
You didn't think
I could make the time, did you?

34:34.530 --> 34:37.617
I think you can, but no, not today.
I don't think you made that time.

34:37.700 --> 34:39.202
Are you saying that I lie?

34:39.285 --> 34:41.037
No, I'm saying you're mistaken.

34:41.120 --> 34:42.622
I'm not mistaken.

34:42.705 --> 34:45.374
Okay, so you're on your sixth run,

34:46.250 --> 34:47.794
you're totally drained,

34:47.877 --> 34:52.548
and you just happen to break
your second record of the day,

34:52.632 --> 34:54.217
right before a crawl.

34:54.300 --> 34:55.426
I don't think so, kid.

34:55.510 --> 34:59.514
You saw the time. I saw you look down.
You have to let me go with you.

34:59.597 --> 35:01.516
You want to find Henry so bad, don't you?

35:01.599 --> 35:02.517
So bad.

35:02.600 --> 35:04.560
Do it. Do it from the tub.

35:05.061 --> 35:06.437
Do it remotely.

35:06.938 --> 35:09.857
You're not coming with me. Not today.

35:10.566 --> 35:11.651
End of story.

35:24.789 --> 35:26.457
Why are you being so hard on her?

35:26.958 --> 35:28.584
I'm not being hard on her.

35:30.378 --> 35:32.171
She's just trying to help.

35:32.255 --> 35:33.714
It'd be great if Will could help,

35:33.798 --> 35:36.259
but you keep that kid
wrapped in bubble wrap.

35:36.342 --> 35:38.302
Come on. That's different.

35:38.386 --> 35:39.762
I mean, El…

35:39.846 --> 35:43.057
Look at her. She's… She's ready.

35:43.558 --> 35:45.852
Thirty-seven crawls.

35:45.935 --> 35:49.188
The only thing I found
down in that damn place are soldiers,

35:49.272 --> 35:50.189
lots of them.

35:50.273 --> 35:52.608
And they're all looking
for one person, El.

35:53.192 --> 35:56.320
So there's no reason to put her life
on the line and bring her down there,

35:56.404 --> 35:59.407
especially not for some recon mission.

35:59.490 --> 36:03.661
Well, if it's just some recon mission,
then what's with all the guns?

36:04.245 --> 36:05.955
It's in case I run into trouble.

36:06.038 --> 36:08.166
-Yeah, or in case you run into him.
-No.

36:09.125 --> 36:12.170
I run into that psychic freak,
I'm tucking tail and running.

36:13.254 --> 36:17.049
I'm nuts. I'm nuts. But I'm not that nuts.

36:22.597 --> 36:26.434
I'm gonna need El.
I know that. I know that.

36:27.351 --> 36:30.938
Which is precisely why
there's no point in risking her life

36:31.439 --> 36:34.192
over some stupid recon crap.

36:36.986 --> 36:41.282
I want her primed, but I want her safe.
Safe until the very last minute, okay?

36:43.159 --> 36:44.535
Yeah, okay.

36:45.828 --> 36:49.290
But her time on that last run,

36:49.790 --> 36:50.791
did she make it?

36:52.585 --> 36:54.128
With a second to spare.

37:34.961 --> 37:36.712
See what Donna was wearing?

37:36.796 --> 37:38.673
She's gone up like two sizes
since last year.

37:38.756 --> 37:40.883
-Yeah, right.
-Jesus Christ!

37:42.051 --> 37:43.010
Oh my God.

37:44.220 --> 37:47.515
It's just a corn snake, dude.
Guys, it's just a corn snake.

37:49.016 --> 37:50.559
You're a pussy, dude.

37:50.643 --> 37:53.271
-Did you piss your pants?
-It's just a snake.

37:54.105 --> 37:56.023
Hey, Andy, is that your new pet?

37:56.857 --> 37:57.858
Don't scare him.

38:17.461 --> 38:18.462
Holly!

38:19.797 --> 38:20.881
Holly!

38:29.724 --> 38:30.850
Holly.

38:32.018 --> 38:34.562
What are you doing?
Come on. I have to get going.

38:34.645 --> 38:36.022
Sorry.

38:37.606 --> 38:39.066
They told me to wait.

38:52.663 --> 38:55.916
Is this about your mystery friend again?

38:56.000 --> 38:57.543
Mr. Whatsit?

39:00.087 --> 39:01.881
He's only trying to help.

39:01.964 --> 39:04.342
Help? How?

39:04.967 --> 39:06.510
By protecting me.

39:06.594 --> 39:10.931
He says that there are
monsters in Hawkins,

39:11.682 --> 39:14.977
and… they like to eat kids like me.

39:15.561 --> 39:17.688
Monsters aren't real, Holly.

39:18.856 --> 39:20.358
I don't believe you.

39:22.777 --> 39:25.196
I know you're scared
because of everything that's happened.

39:25.780 --> 39:30.034
With the crazy stories people tell,
I mean, I get scared sometimes too.

39:30.117 --> 39:31.160
No, you don't.

39:31.243 --> 39:32.370
Are you kidding?

39:32.453 --> 39:34.455
Everyone in Hawkins is scared shitless.

39:34.538 --> 39:36.290
Anyone who says they aren't
are full of it.

39:36.374 --> 39:39.585
Like that mouth breather in your class…
What's his name again?

39:39.668 --> 39:41.587
-Derek?
-Yeah, Derek.

39:42.296 --> 39:44.173
He probably wets his bed every night.

39:47.134 --> 39:49.053
Know who I turn to when I get scared?

39:58.896 --> 39:59.730
Mike the Brave.

40:00.314 --> 40:02.608
He goes on adventures
called dungeon crawls.

40:02.691 --> 40:04.276
What's a dungeon crawl?

40:04.360 --> 40:06.904
Basically, he explores
these underground worlds,

40:06.987 --> 40:10.699
where he fights monsters,
evil wizards, sorcerers and stuff.

40:10.783 --> 40:13.327
But Mike the Brave is never scared.

40:13.411 --> 40:17.373
So whenever I'm feeling
frightened or nervous,

40:17.456 --> 40:19.333
I just imagine that he's at my side,

40:19.417 --> 40:20.418
and I feel better.

40:21.085 --> 40:25.047
So maybe the next time you get scared,
you don't need this Mr. Whatsit.

40:25.714 --> 40:28.801
Maybe you just need Holly the Heroic.

40:29.677 --> 40:31.262
Holly the Heroic?

40:32.680 --> 40:34.807
I was gonna to wait a few more years, but…

40:44.692 --> 40:47.778
She's a cleric,
which means she has divine powers.

40:47.862 --> 40:50.364
She can cast spells of protection
to ward against evil spirits,

40:50.448 --> 40:53.742
and even cooler,
she can cast a dimension door,

40:53.826 --> 40:56.078
which can teleport you
to anywhere you visualize.

40:57.746 --> 40:58.706
I mean, come on.

40:58.789 --> 41:01.041
Can this lame-o Mr. Whatsit
do any of this?

41:01.125 --> 41:03.043
No.

41:04.795 --> 41:07.965
She'll keep you safe. I promise.

41:12.720 --> 41:14.680
It was this weird feeling.

41:15.556 --> 41:18.350
Like something
I really haven't felt before.

41:18.851 --> 41:21.979
Mike thinks it could mean
that maybe Vecna's close,

41:22.062 --> 41:24.857
that he's finally re-emerged.

41:25.357 --> 41:29.028
And if he has,
maybe we'll find him tonight.

41:32.072 --> 41:33.616
What do you think, Lucas?

41:36.035 --> 41:38.913
Yeah, I think
we'll find him this time for sure.

41:42.041 --> 41:43.292
You wanna play the tape?

41:43.375 --> 41:45.878
I'm gonna go grab a Coke
or something caffeinated,

41:45.961 --> 41:48.130
because it's gonna be a long night.

41:48.214 --> 41:49.381
You want one?

41:49.882 --> 41:51.800
No. I'm good. Thanks.

42:33.133 --> 42:34.426
Robin!

42:35.803 --> 42:37.012
Rockin' Robin!

42:41.809 --> 42:44.478
Okay. So I have good news,
and I have bad news.

42:44.562 --> 42:45.771
What are you doing here?

42:45.854 --> 42:48.357
A good friend once said,
"Bad news first, always."

42:48.440 --> 42:50.818
So I have to cancel our date tonight.

42:51.819 --> 42:52.653
Of course.

42:52.736 --> 42:56.365
But the good news is
I made us a reservation.

42:56.448 --> 42:59.368
8:00 p.m. tomorrow night at Enzo's.

43:01.620 --> 43:05.332
Enzo's? Okay, how exactly
are we gonna be able to afford that?

43:05.416 --> 43:07.543
You mean how am I going to afford it?

43:07.626 --> 43:09.545
Because you, my dear,
are paying for nothing.

43:10.379 --> 43:11.380
Double how, then?

43:11.463 --> 43:13.841
I stole money off the dead guy
they just wheeled out.

43:13.924 --> 43:15.676
That's not funny.
His name was Mr. Pentergast,

43:15.759 --> 43:16.719
and he was very nice.

43:16.802 --> 43:18.053
And very rich.

43:18.137 --> 43:21.849
-Robin…
-Look, dinner's on me, okay?

43:21.932 --> 43:26.645
But, uh, maybe for dessert,
I could… I could see you in this hat,

43:26.729 --> 43:29.023
and, like, only this hat.

43:29.773 --> 43:32.484
I hate you. I…

43:41.327 --> 43:43.162
Was that on purpose?

43:43.746 --> 43:45.581
-Totally.
-That's so sexy.

43:47.082 --> 43:50.419
So, there any chance
I could get you to wear this outfit?

43:50.502 --> 43:51.462
But that's…

44:02.348 --> 44:03.265
Who is that?

44:03.766 --> 44:04.725
Shit.

44:28.957 --> 44:33.212
Don't worry, Eddie.
Eventually they'll get bored.

45:11.375 --> 45:13.794
You should really keep a better eye
on your pets, Henderson.

45:13.877 --> 45:17.756
It's dangerous out there.
They shouldn't be left alone like that.

45:17.840 --> 45:20.551
Hey there, freak. Long time no see.

45:20.634 --> 45:21.635
Hiya.

45:28.183 --> 45:31.520
Something funny, Henderson?

45:31.603 --> 45:34.064
No, I… I was just thinking.

45:34.565 --> 45:36.233
In Eddie's last campaign,

45:37.735 --> 45:40.988
I defeated Vecna's lead acolyte
by casting Prismatic Spray.

45:42.489 --> 45:44.158
One D8 turned up a 7.

45:44.867 --> 45:45.784
Violet.

45:46.368 --> 45:48.704
Is that supposed to be English, freak?

45:49.455 --> 45:53.959
Well, violet Prismatic Spray
is the deadliest. You know why?

45:55.878 --> 45:57.463
It causes blindness.

46:00.090 --> 46:01.091
Hey!

46:29.369 --> 46:31.288
Hellfire dies with you, Henderson.

46:31.955 --> 46:33.040
And it dies tonight.

46:46.845 --> 46:50.390
Dustin, this is Lucas. Do you copy? Over.

46:50.474 --> 46:53.060
Dustin, do you copy? Over.

46:54.186 --> 46:57.397
Dustin, you're an hour late, man.
You're making us nervous.

46:57.481 --> 46:59.191
We need you here at the Squawk.

46:59.733 --> 47:02.444
Dustin, if you can hear us,
please respond. Over.

47:02.528 --> 47:04.863
I got off the phone with his mom.
She hasn't heard from him.

47:04.947 --> 47:07.616
-Christ, Henderson.
-He'll show. He always shows.

47:07.699 --> 47:08.617
Try him again.

47:09.117 --> 47:11.745
Come in, Dustin. Are you there?
Earth to Dustin.

47:11.829 --> 47:13.997
This is serious, man. Quit playing.
We can't wait around.

47:17.584 --> 47:19.336
Get your ass to the Squawk.

47:19.419 --> 47:21.547
We can't wait around.
We need you here now.

47:21.630 --> 47:23.298
This is not funny. Are you there?

47:24.383 --> 47:26.176
Dustin, is everything okay?

47:26.802 --> 47:29.680
-Do you think Dustin is okay?
-Dustin!

47:30.597 --> 47:31.598
I hope so.

47:32.933 --> 47:34.476
He was acting weird today.

47:35.394 --> 47:37.145
Weird how?

47:37.729 --> 47:42.150
Just angry, scared, reckless. Not himself.

47:43.360 --> 47:44.820
Hopper's the same.

47:45.529 --> 47:46.697
Not himself.

47:49.783 --> 47:52.619
Maybe it's just getting to us, you know?

47:52.703 --> 47:56.832
Being… Being stuck in here,
not knowing where Vecna is,

47:56.915 --> 47:58.041
no end in sight.

47:58.125 --> 48:00.836
I mean, we're really starting to lose it.

48:00.919 --> 48:03.797
I mean, we really need to catch a break.

48:04.840 --> 48:08.135
And maybe we will.
Because earlier, Will had a feeling.

48:08.886 --> 48:11.388
-If Will has a feeling--
-Then it means something.

48:11.471 --> 48:13.640
So… So, maybe tonight's our break.

48:13.724 --> 48:15.142
Maybe even our last crawl.

48:15.893 --> 48:18.854
We find Vecna,
and we end this once and for all.

48:22.566 --> 48:23.901
And then what happens?

48:23.984 --> 48:26.904
You mean after you totally demolish Vecna?

48:28.363 --> 48:32.284
In my campaigns, if the party wins,
then they all live happily ever after.

48:33.410 --> 48:34.953
Happily how?

48:35.621 --> 48:40.792
Well, usually what happens is the party
doesn't return to their local village,

48:40.876 --> 48:42.753
because too much has happened.

48:43.503 --> 48:44.880
They've seen too much.

48:44.963 --> 48:48.216
So they travel to a faraway land,
a… a peaceful land,

48:48.300 --> 48:52.137
somewhere beautiful,
with like three waterfalls or something,

48:52.846 --> 48:55.557
and they all start again, together.

48:57.100 --> 49:01.188
Do you think that could be real for us?

49:01.813 --> 49:03.690
Yeah, of course.

49:04.942 --> 49:09.821
I mean, not the three waterfalls part.
But the other stuff, yeah, of course.

49:10.948 --> 49:14.451
If Vecna's gone, then what's stopping us?

49:16.745 --> 49:19.373
Hey, lovebirds! Chief's almost ready.

49:19.456 --> 49:21.625
Let's do this. Come on.

49:35.514 --> 49:36.515
Thank you.

49:39.643 --> 49:40.644
Here.

49:40.727 --> 49:41.728
Good luck.

49:43.730 --> 49:45.440
-Tag's active.
-Copy.

49:47.734 --> 49:50.028
Harrington, you getting any signal?
Tag is active.

49:51.238 --> 49:52.698
Yeah, just give me a second.

50:01.957 --> 50:04.042
Hey, anybody know
how Henderson's wheelie thing works?

50:04.918 --> 50:05.919
Uh, any ideas?

50:06.003 --> 50:08.839
There's a safety lock.
Look for a small switch under the wheel.

50:08.922 --> 50:11.717
There should be
a safety lock under the wheel.

50:11.800 --> 50:14.261
Safety lock, real necessary.

50:24.312 --> 50:25.313
Okay.

50:29.401 --> 50:30.986
Okay, getting a signal.

50:31.486 --> 50:33.238
It's pretty quiet, though.

50:42.914 --> 50:45.500
Okay, signal's holding a steady 90 dB.

50:45.584 --> 50:49.171
But how am I supposed to monitor this
and drive without Henderson?

50:49.755 --> 50:52.090
Uh, hear anything from Inspector Gadget?

50:52.174 --> 50:53.175
Nothing.

50:53.258 --> 50:55.469
I can do it. I… I can monitor.

50:55.552 --> 50:56.845
No. You're staying here.

50:56.928 --> 50:59.598
Mom, I helped Dustin set up the antenna.
I know how to work it.

50:59.681 --> 51:02.184
Out of the question.
It… It's just a wheel.

51:02.267 --> 51:03.393
It's not just a wheel.

51:03.477 --> 51:05.395
Jonathan, you… you can work it, right?

51:08.148 --> 51:09.983
Yeah, yeah. I mean, I think so.

51:10.067 --> 51:12.277
You better not think. You better know.

51:12.360 --> 51:14.154
You lose me out there,
I'm not coming home.

51:15.030 --> 51:15.989
I can handle it.

51:32.339 --> 51:34.299
You comfortable back there, Byers?

51:35.592 --> 51:37.219
Or you want me to get you a pillow?

51:38.136 --> 51:39.721
Just focus on driving.

52:05.205 --> 52:07.833
Try to get back to me in one piece, okay?

52:12.963 --> 52:14.256
What?

52:14.840 --> 52:16.424
Sorry, I'm just looking at you.

52:16.925 --> 52:18.552
You get more beautiful every day.

52:21.388 --> 52:22.681
How is that fair?

52:23.390 --> 52:25.183
You didn't answer my question.

52:25.267 --> 52:26.476
I know.

52:27.310 --> 52:28.728
You didn't answer mine.

53:06.099 --> 53:10.729
Look, she was standing
at the fence, talking into thin air.

53:10.812 --> 53:12.480
She probably was talking to herself.

53:12.564 --> 53:14.232
…standing there talking to nobody.

53:14.316 --> 53:18.278
Well, she's hardly the first child
to have an imaginary friend, Karen.

53:18.361 --> 53:20.655
I wouldn't be so worried
if she was five years old,

53:20.739 --> 53:22.199
but she's not five anymore, is she?

53:22.282 --> 53:25.285
In fact, do you even know
how old your daughter is?

53:25.368 --> 53:27.662
-Oh, you don't even know how old she is!
-You're ridiculous.

53:27.746 --> 53:29.789
I'm not talking to you
when you're like this.

53:29.873 --> 53:32.125
First one tonight,
or already onto number two?

53:32.209 --> 53:33.585
Does it matter?

54:53.581 --> 54:56.584
Squawk to Crow's Nest, anything? Over.

54:56.668 --> 54:58.545
Negative, not a peep.

55:05.176 --> 55:06.428
Do you have to chew so loud?

55:07.012 --> 55:08.388
Snipers chew gum.

55:08.471 --> 55:09.806
You're not a sniper.

55:12.267 --> 55:15.645
Package incoming.
Four trucks, outer east gate on Main.

55:16.271 --> 55:20.025
We got action.
Four trucks, outer east gate on Main.

55:27.073 --> 55:28.366
The hole! Clear the hole.

55:30.118 --> 55:32.120
Burners, prepare to deploy.

55:32.203 --> 55:35.623
On my mark! Move, move, move.

55:35.707 --> 55:37.167
Burners heading for the gate.

55:40.587 --> 55:43.757
Burn commencing in five, four,

55:44.466 --> 55:47.177
three, two,

55:47.761 --> 55:49.220
and boom!

56:05.904 --> 56:07.030
Trucks moving in.

56:07.113 --> 56:08.573
Trucks moving in.

56:27.425 --> 56:28.426
Am I clear?

56:31.096 --> 56:33.348
-Clear to the east.
-East is clear.

56:34.057 --> 56:35.100
And to the west?

56:38.311 --> 56:40.188
Hold. We got a straggler.

56:40.980 --> 56:41.815
Come on.

56:41.898 --> 56:43.483
Get the hell out of there.

56:43.566 --> 56:44.567
Come on.

56:49.030 --> 56:50.323
Clear.

57:01.835 --> 57:02.752
He's in.

57:02.836 --> 57:04.170
He's in.

57:16.641 --> 57:18.184
Open sesame.

57:38.746 --> 57:40.039
He's flipped.

57:48.631 --> 57:50.133
Jonathan, signal?

57:57.474 --> 57:58.308
Snagged it.

58:00.143 --> 58:02.020
-Should I move?
-No.

58:02.604 --> 58:03.521
Hold.

58:04.689 --> 58:06.941
Hold. Hold.

58:08.401 --> 58:09.861
Hold.

58:10.445 --> 58:11.279
Go!

58:18.328 --> 58:20.038
Van is on the move.

58:28.171 --> 58:30.715
Hopper, can you hear us okay?

58:30.798 --> 58:32.592
Yeah, yeah, loud and clear.

58:33.259 --> 58:35.595
Good, good. Okay, hard part's over.

58:35.678 --> 58:39.098
I mean, speak for yourself.
I still gotta jump out of this thing.

58:39.599 --> 58:42.310
And is it me,
or are we moving faster than normal?

58:42.393 --> 58:43.436
A little faster.

58:43.520 --> 58:46.231
Just aim for the grass.

58:46.314 --> 58:49.359
I was gonna go for the asphalt,
but now that you mention the grass--

58:57.033 --> 58:58.743
What's going on? Hopper?

58:59.452 --> 59:00.870
-We're losing him!
-Wait, what?

59:00.954 --> 59:02.372
Wait! Stop! Stop!

59:13.383 --> 59:14.509
We got him.

59:17.595 --> 59:19.097
Hopper, do you copy?

59:19.681 --> 59:20.598
Hopper!

59:21.474 --> 59:23.059
Yeah, I copy.

59:23.142 --> 59:24.727
What the hell happened?

59:24.811 --> 59:27.605
I don't know. We just slammed to a stop.

59:27.689 --> 59:29.732
Wh… Why would they stop?

59:30.400 --> 59:31.526
The soldiers…

59:32.902 --> 59:34.195
they know he's there.

59:35.488 --> 59:36.781
We don't know that.

59:43.663 --> 59:45.623
What's going on over there?

59:49.961 --> 59:51.087
There are too many.

59:51.796 --> 59:53.214
He can't take them.

1:00:12.317 --> 1:00:13.693
Whoa!

1:00:35.965 --> 1:00:37.925
-The hell's happening?
-I don't know.

1:01:26.599 --> 1:01:27.809
Will! No!

1:01:27.892 --> 1:01:28.851
Honey!

1:01:28.935 --> 1:01:32.522
Will! Will! Will!

1:02:12.353 --> 1:02:13.771
Squawk, do you copy?

1:02:14.647 --> 1:02:16.607
Joyce? Anyone?

1:02:36.669 --> 1:02:39.630
Will, Will, come back! Come on, honey.

1:02:39.714 --> 1:02:42.216
Will, come back. Come back.

1:02:42.300 --> 1:02:43.468
Will, come on.

1:02:43.551 --> 1:02:45.553
Will! Will! Wake up!

1:03:01.736 --> 1:03:04.739
Come back! Come back!

1:03:05.448 --> 1:03:07.241
Will, sweetie. It's okay.

1:03:07.325 --> 1:03:08.785
Mom!

1:03:08.868 --> 1:03:11.078
It's okay. It's okay.

1:03:11.829 --> 1:03:13.998
I'm here. I'm here.

1:03:14.081 --> 1:03:16.626
It's okay. Just breathe. Just breathe.

1:03:17.919 --> 1:03:18.920
What happened?

1:03:22.256 --> 1:03:23.341
I saw it.

1:03:24.133 --> 1:03:25.760
What? What did you see?

1:03:25.843 --> 1:03:27.386
The Demogorgon.

1:03:28.221 --> 1:03:31.682
It's coming. It's coming for them.

1:03:32.266 --> 1:03:34.602
For who? Who's them?

1:03:43.528 --> 1:03:44.445
Robin, stay here.

1:03:44.529 --> 1:03:47.198
Contact Hopper, the boys.
Tell everyone what's going on.

1:03:47.281 --> 1:03:48.241
Right. Right.

1:03:48.324 --> 1:03:50.535
-Think you can get the power back on?
-I can try.

1:03:50.618 --> 1:03:53.871
You do, you call my house
and tell everyone to get the hell out.

1:03:53.955 --> 1:03:54.789
Okay.

1:05:22.001 --> 1:05:23.085
Mom!

1:05:25.463 --> 1:05:26.464
Mom!

1:05:50.154 --> 1:05:52.323
I said upside down, you're turning me

1:05:52.406 --> 1:05:54.784
You're giving love instinctively

1:05:54.867 --> 1:05:57.036
'Round and 'round, you're turning me

1:05:59.330 --> 1:06:01.123
Upside down

1:06:02.124 --> 1:06:05.628
Boy, you turn me inside out

1:06:05.711 --> 1:06:08.130
And 'round and 'round

1:06:08.214 --> 1:06:10.049
Upside down

1:06:11.050 --> 1:06:14.595
Boy, you turn me inside out

1:06:14.679 --> 1:06:16.722
And 'round and 'round

1:06:18.015 --> 1:06:22.353
Instinctively, you give to me
The love that I need

1:06:22.436 --> 1:06:25.773
I cherish the moments with you

1:06:26.816 --> 1:06:28.651
Respectfully, I say to thee

1:06:28.734 --> 1:06:31.153
I'm aware that you're cheating

1:06:31.237 --> 1:06:34.240
When no one makes me feel like you do

1:06:34.740 --> 1:06:36.492
Upside down

1:06:37.535 --> 1:06:41.038
Boy, you turn me inside out

1:06:41.122 --> 1:06:43.457
And 'round and 'round

1:06:43.541 --> 1:06:45.292
Upside down

1:06:46.293 --> 1:06:49.964
Boy, you turn me inside out

1:06:50.047 --> 1:06:51.966
And 'round and 'round

1:06:53.342 --> 1:06:55.386
I know you got charm and appeal

1:06:55.469 --> 1:06:57.680
You always play the field

1:06:57.763 --> 1:07:00.850
I'm crazy to think you're all mine

1:07:02.143 --> 1:07:06.188
As long as the sun continues to shine

1:07:06.272 --> 1:07:09.942
There's a place in my heart for you
That's the bottom line

1:07:10.026 --> 1:07:12.028
Upside down

1:07:12.695 --> 1:07:16.198
Boy, you turn me inside out

1:07:16.282 --> 1:07:18.284
And 'round and 'round

1:07:18.868 --> 1:07:20.870
Upside down

1:07:21.537 --> 1:07:25.166
Boy, you turn me inside out

1:07:25.249 --> 1:07:27.418
And 'round and 'round

1:07:28.544 --> 1:07:32.923
Instinctively, you give to me
The love that I need

1:07:33.007 --> 1:07:36.260
I cherish the moments with you

1:07:37.386 --> 1:07:39.138
Respectfully, I say to thee

1:07:39.221 --> 1:07:41.682
I'm aware that you're cheating

1:07:41.766 --> 1:07:44.518
But no one makes me feel like you do

1:07:45.269 --> 1:07:47.271
Upside down

1:07:47.938 --> 1:07:51.525
Boy, you turn me inside out

1:07:51.609 --> 1:07:53.944
And 'round, 'round

1:07:54.028 --> 1:07:55.863
Upside down

1:07:56.822 --> 1:08:00.284
Boy, you turn me inside out

1:08:00.367 --> 1:11:28.059
And 'round and 'round
